cjnAtalk.name: cjnAtalk
cjnAtalk.contactinfo: Erick Crowell -- ecrowell@lucent.com Raj Duggal (Group Leader) -- rduggal@lucent.com Simon Fang sfang@lucent.com Michael C. Cambria -- mcambria@lucent.com
cjnAtalk.description: Cajun Private Apple Talk Routing MIB

cjnAtIsEnabled.name: cjnAtIsEnabled
cjnAtIsEnabled.description: Enables Apple Talk Routing services on this device.

cjnAtGlobalStatsReset.name: cjnAtGlobalStatsReset
cjnAtGlobalStatsReset.description: When set to the value enable (2) all Apple Talk Global Statistics are reset to zero after which the value of this MIB object returns to disable(1)

cjnAtIfNextZoneIndex.name: cjnAtIfNextZoneIndex
cjnAtIfNextZoneIndex.description: The next AtIfZoneIndex value to be used to create a new row.

cjnAtIfZoneTable.name: cjnAtIfZoneTable
cjnAtIfZoneTable.description: A list of Apple Talk Interface Zone Entries for this entity.

cjnAtIfZoneEntry.name: cjnAtIfZoneEntry
cjnAtIfZoneEntry.description: The Interface Zone Entry to a particular port.

cjnAtIfZoneIndex.name: cjnAtIfZoneIndex
cjnAtIfZoneIndex.description: An integer that is unique to the IfZoneName that is present in this entry. For any given zone name, every zipEntry that has an equal zone name will have the same IfZoneIndex.

cjnAtIfZoneName.name: cjnAtIfZoneName
cjnAtIfZoneName.description: The ASCII zone name of this entry.

cjnAtIfZoneDefault.name: cjnAtIfZoneDefault
cjnAtIfZoneDefault.description: When set to the value yes (1) this zone name is the default zone name for the port. When set to no(2), this zone name is not the default zone name for the port.

cjnAtIfZoneRowStatus.name: cjnAtIfZoneRowStatus
cjnAtIfZoneRowStatus.description: The status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active on this interface. notInService(2) -- Configured on Interface but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface entry NOT FULLY configured. createAndGo(4), -- NOT SUPPORTED. createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnAtStatRtTable.name: cjnAtStatRtTable
cjnAtStatRtTable.description: A list of Apple Talk Static Route Entries for this entity.

cjnAtStatRtEntry.name: cjnAtStatRtEntry
cjnAtStatRtEntry.description: The Static Route Entry to a particular network range.

cjnAtStatRtRangeStart.name: cjnAtStatRtRangeStart
cjnAtStatRtRangeStart.description: The first DDP network address in the network range to which this routing entry pertains. This is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order.

cjnAtStatRtRangeEnd.name: cjnAtStatRtRangeEnd
cjnAtStatRtRangeEnd.description: The last DDP network address in the network range to which this routing entry pertains. This is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order. If the network to which this routing entry pertains is a Phase 1 network or a non-extended network, the value for rtmpRangeEnd shall be two octets of zero.

cjnAtStatRtRowStatus.name: cjnAtStatRtRowStatus
cjnAtStatRtRowStatus.description: The Ddp Address of the next hop in the route to this entry's destination network.

cjnAtStatRtNextHop.name: cjnAtStatRtNextHop
cjnAtStatRtNextHop.description: The Ddp Address of the next hop in the route to this entry's destination network.

cjnAtStatRtType.name: cjnAtStatRtType
cjnAtStatRtType.description: The type of Static Route Entry.

cjnAtNextStatRtZoneIndex.name: cjnAtNextStatRtZoneIndex
cjnAtNextStatRtZoneIndex.description: The next StatRtZoneIndex value to be used for row creation.

cjnAtStatRtZoneTable.name: cjnAtStatRtZoneTable
cjnAtStatRtZoneTable.description: A list of Apple Talk Static Route Zone Entries for this entity.

cjnAtStatRtZoneEntry.name: cjnAtStatRtZoneEntry
cjnAtStatRtZoneEntry.description: The Zone Entry to a particular Static Route.

cjnAtStatRtZoneIndex.name: cjnAtStatRtZoneIndex
cjnAtStatRtZoneIndex.description: An integer that is unique to the StatRtZoneName that is present in this entry. For any given zone name, every zipEntry that has an equal zone name will have the same StatRtZoneIndex.

cjnAtStatRtZoneName.name: cjnAtStatRtZoneName
cjnAtStatRtZoneName.description: The ASCII zone name of this entry.

cjnAtStatRtZoneRowStatus.name: cjnAtStatRtZoneRowStatus
cjnAtStatRtZoneRowStatus.description: The status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active on this interface. notInService(2) -- Configured on Interface but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface entry NOT FULLY configured. createAndGo(4), -- NOT SUPPORTED. createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnAarpReset.name: cjnAarpReset
cjnAarpReset.description: When set to the value enable (2) all Apple Talk AARP Table is cleared, after which the value of this MIB object returns to disable(1)

cjnAarpTable.name: cjnAarpTable
cjnAarpTable.description: The AppleTalk Address Translation Table contains an equivalence of AppleTalk Network Addresses to the link layer physical address.

cjnAarpEntry.name: cjnAarpEntry
cjnAarpEntry.description: Each entry contains one AppleTalk Network Address to physical address equivalence.

cjnAarpRowStatus.name: cjnAarpRowStatus
cjnAarpRowStatus.description: The status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active on this interface. notInService(2) -- Configured on Interface but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface entry NOT FULLY configured. createAndGo(4), -- NOT SUPPORTED. createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnAarpNetAddress.name: cjnAarpNetAddress
cjnAarpNetAddress.description: The AppleTalk Network Address corresponding to the media-dependent physical address. Note: When cjnAarpType is either broadcast or multicast, this field represents only the beginning network in the network range.

cjnAarpDescr.name: cjnAarpDescr
cjnAarpDescr.description: A text string containing information about the port. This string is intended for presentation to a human; it must not contain anything but printable ASCII characters.

cjnAarpType.name: cjnAarpType
cjnAarpType.description: The type of this AARP entry.

cjnAarpTtl.name: cjnAarpTtl
cjnAarpTtl.description: The TTL of this AARP entry.

cjnRtmpReset.name: cjnRtmpReset
cjnRtmpReset.description: When set to the value enable (2) all Apple Talk Route Table is cleared, after which the value of this MIB object returns to disable(1)

cjnRtmpTable.name: cjnRtmpTable
cjnRtmpTable.description: A list of Routing Table Maintenance Protocol entries for this entity.

cjnRtmpEntry.name: cjnRtmpEntry
cjnRtmpEntry.description: The route entry to a particular network range.

cjnRtmpRangeStart.name: cjnRtmpRangeStart
cjnRtmpRangeStart.description: The first DDP network address in the network range to which this routing entry pertains. This is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order.

cjnRtmpRangeEnd.name: cjnRtmpRangeEnd
cjnRtmpRangeEnd.description: The last DDP network address in the network range to which this routing entry pertains. This is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order. If the network to which this routing entry pertains is a Phase 1 network or a non-extended network, the value for rtmpRangeEnd shall be two octets of zero.

cjnRtmpNextHop.name: cjnRtmpNextHop
cjnRtmpNextHop.description: The next hop in the route to this entry's destination network.

cjnRtmpHops.name: cjnRtmpHops
cjnRtmpHops.description: The number of hops required to reach the destination network to which this routing entry pertains.

cjnRtmpState.name: cjnRtmpState
cjnRtmpState.description: The status of the information contained in this route entry. Setting this object to the value bad(4) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the rtmpTable. That is, it effectively disassociates the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive from agents tabular information corresponding to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant rtmpState object.

cjnRtmpOwner.name: cjnRtmpOwner
cjnRtmpOwner.description: The Owner of this Route Entry.

cjnRtmpDescr.name: cjnRtmpDescr
cjnRtmpDescr.description: A text string containing information about the port used to forward to the next hop. This string is intended for presentation to a human; it must not contain anything but printable ASCII characters.

cjnRtmpRowStatus.name: cjnRtmpRowStatus
cjnRtmpRowStatus.description: The status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active on this interface. notInService(2) -- Configured on Interface but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface entry NOT FULLY configured. createAndGo(4), -- NOT SUPPORTED. createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnZipTable.name: cjnZipTable
cjnZipTable.description: The table of zone information for reachable AppleTalk networks.

cjnZipEntry.name: cjnZipEntry
cjnZipEntry.description: An entry of zone information for a particular zone and network combination.

cjnZipZoneIndex.name: cjnZipZoneIndex
cjnZipZoneIndex.description: An integer that is unique to the zipZoneName that is present in this entry. For any given zone name, every zipEntry that has an equal zone name will have the same zipZoneIndex.

cjnZipZoneName.name: cjnZipZoneName
cjnZipZoneName.description: The ASCII zone name of this entry.

cjnZipZoneNetStart.name: cjnZipZoneNetStart
cjnZipZoneNetStart.description: The network that starts the range for this entry. This address is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order.

cjnZipZoneNetEnd.name: cjnZipZoneNetEnd
cjnZipZoneNetEnd.description: The network that ends the range for this entry. This address is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order. If the network to which this zip entry pertains is a Phase 1 network or a non-extended network, the value for zipZoneNetEnd shall be two bytes of zero.

cjnNbpTable.name: cjnNbpTable
cjnNbpTable.description: The table of NBP services registered on this entity.

cjnNbpEntry.name: cjnNbpEntry
cjnNbpEntry.description: The description of an NBP service registered on this entity.

cjnNbpIndex.name: cjnNbpIndex
cjnNbpIndex.description: The index of this NBP entry. This value ranges from 1 to the number of NBP entries currently registered on this entity.

cjnNbpObject.name: cjnNbpObject
cjnNbpObject.description: The name of the service described by this entity.

cjnNbpType.name: cjnNbpType
cjnNbpType.description: The type of the service described by this entity.

cjnNbpZone.name: cjnNbpZone
cjnNbpZone.description: The zone the service described by this entity is registered in.

cjnNbpState.name: cjnNbpState
cjnNbpState.description: The state of this NBP entry. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the nbpTable. That is, it effectively disassociates the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive from agents tabular information corresponding to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant nbpState object.

cjnAtEchoRequests.name: cjnAtEchoRequests
cjnAtEchoRequests.description: The number of AppleTalk echo requests received.

cjnAtEchoReplies.name: cjnAtEchoReplies
cjnAtEchoReplies.description: The number of AppleTalk echo replies sent.

cjnAtEchoTimeouts.name: cjnAtEchoTimeouts
cjnAtEchoTimeouts.description: The number of AppleTalk echo request timeouts.

cjnAtEchoSend.name: cjnAtEchoSend
cjnAtEchoSend.description: Causes an Apple Talk Echo Request to be sent to the supplied Apple Talk Address.

cjnAtEchoReset.name: cjnAtEchoReset
cjnAtEchoReset.description: When set to the value enable (2) all Apple Talk Echo Counters are reset to zero after which the value of this MIB object returns to disable(1)

cjnDdpOutRequests.name: cjnDdpOutRequests
cjnDdpOutRequests.description: The total number of DDP datagrams which were supplied to DDP by local DDP clients in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ddpForwRequests.

cjnDdpOutShorts.name: cjnDdpOutShorts
cjnDdpOutShorts.description: The total number of short DDP datagrams which were transmitted from this entity.

cjnDdpOutLongs.name: cjnDdpOutLongs
cjnDdpOutLongs.description: The total number of long DDP datagrams which were transmitted from this entity.

cjnDdpInReceives.name: cjnDdpInReceives
cjnDdpInReceives.description: The total number of input datagrams received by DDP, including those received in error.

cjnDdpForwRequests.name: cjnDdpForwRequests
cjnDdpForwRequests.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final DDP destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination.

cjnDdpInLocalDatagrams.name: cjnDdpInLocalDatagrams
cjnDdpInLocalDatagrams.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams for which this entity was their final DDP destination.

cjnDdpNoProtocolHandlers.name: cjnDdpNoProtocolHandlers
cjnDdpNoProtocolHandlers.description: The total number of DDP datagrams addressed to this entity that were addressed to an upper layer protocol for which no protocol handler existed.

cjnDdpOutNoRoutes.name: cjnDdpOutNoRoutes
cjnDdpOutNoRoutes.description: The total number of DDP datagrams dropped because a route could not be found to their final destination.

cjnDdpTooShortErrors.name: cjnDdpTooShortErrors
cjnDdpTooShortErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because the received data length was less than the data length specified in the DDP header or the received data length was less than the length of the expected DDP header.

cjnDdpTooLongErrors.name: cjnDdpTooLongErrors
cjnDdpTooLongErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because the received data length was greater than the data length specified in the DDP header or because they exceeded the maximum DDP datagram size.

cjnDdpBroadcastErrors.name: cjnDdpBroadcastErrors
cjnDdpBroadcastErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because this entity was not their final destination and they were addressed to the link level broadcast.

cjnDdpShortDDPErrors.name: cjnDdpShortDDPErrors
cjnDdpShortDDPErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because this entity was not their final destination and their type was short DDP.

cjnDdpHopCountErrors.name: cjnDdpHopCountErrors
cjnDdpHopCountErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because this entity was not their final destination and their hop count would exceed 15.

cjnDdpChecksumErrors.name: cjnDdpChecksumErrors
cjnDdpChecksumErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because of a checksum error.

cjnDdpAarpRqRcv.name: cjnDdpAarpRqRcv
cjnDdpAarpRqRcv.description: The total number of input AARP Requests Received.

cjnDdpAarpReplyRcv.name: cjnDdpAarpReplyRcv
cjnDdpAarpReplyRcv.description: The total number of input AARP Replies Received.

cjnDdpAarpRqTx.name: cjnDdpAarpRqTx
cjnDdpAarpRqTx.description: The total number of output AARP Requests Transmitted.

cjnDdpAarpReplyTx.name: cjnDdpAarpReplyTx
cjnDdpAarpReplyTx.description: The total number of output AARP Replies Transmitted.

cjnDdpAarpBadPdu.name: cjnDdpAarpBadPdu
cjnDdpAarpBadPdu.description: The total number of bad AARP PDU.

cjnDdpCfgAddrError.name: cjnDdpCfgAddrError
cjnDdpCfgAddrError.description: The total number of configuration address errors.

cjnDdpCfgZoneError.name: cjnDdpCfgZoneError
cjnDdpCfgZoneError.description: The total number of configuration zone errors.

cjnDdpEchoRqRcv.name: cjnDdpEchoRqRcv
cjnDdpEchoRqRcv.description: The total number of input Echo Requests Received.

cjnDdpEchoReplyRcv.name: cjnDdpEchoReplyRcv
cjnDdpEchoReplyRcv.description: The total number of input Echo Replies Received.

cjnDdpEchoRqTx.name: cjnDdpEchoRqTx
cjnDdpEchoRqTx.description: The total number of output Echo Requests Transmitted.

cjnAtPortNextIndex.name: cjnAtPortNextIndex
cjnAtPortNextIndex.description: The next cjnAtPortIndex to be used for row creation.

cjnAtPortTable.name: cjnAtPortTable
cjnAtPortTable.description: A list of Cajun AppleTalk ports for this entity.

cjnAtPortEntry.name: cjnAtPortEntry
cjnAtPortEntry.description: The description of one of the Cajun AppleTalk ports on this entity.

cjnAtPortIndex.name: cjnAtPortIndex
cjnAtPortIndex.description: A unique value for each AppleTalk port. Its value is between 1 and the total number of AppleTalk ports. The value for each port must remain constant at least from the re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

cjnAtPortRowStatus.name: cjnAtPortRowStatus
cjnAtPortRowStatus.description: The Status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active on this interface. notInService(2) -- Configured on Interface but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface entry NOT FULLY configured. createAndGo(4), -- NOT SUPPORTED. createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnAtPortDescr.name: cjnAtPortDescr
cjnAtPortDescr.description: A text string containing information about the port. This string is intended for presentation to a human; it must not contain anything but printable ASCII characters.

cjnAtPortMetric.name: cjnAtPortMetric
cjnAtPortMetric.description: The metric assigned to this port.

cjnAtPortFrameType.name: cjnAtPortFrameType
cjnAtPortFrameType.description: The type of Ethernet Frames to be used by the port for Apple Talk.

cjnAtPortNetStart.name: cjnAtPortNetStart
cjnAtPortNetStart.description: The first AppleTalk network address in the range configured for this port. This is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order.

cjnAtPortNetEnd.name: cjnAtPortNetEnd
cjnAtPortNetEnd.description: The last AppleTalk network address in the range configured for this port. This is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order. If the network to which this AppleTalk port is connected is a Phase 1 network or a non-extended network, the value for atportNetEnd shall be two octets of zero.

cjnAtPortNetAddress.name: cjnAtPortNetAddress
cjnAtPortNetAddress.description: The AppleTalk network address configured for this port.

cjnAtPortAdminState.name: cjnAtPortAdminState
cjnAtPortAdminState.description: The configuration status of this port.

cjnAtPortIfIndex.name: cjnAtPortIfIndex
cjnAtPortIfIndex.description: The physical interface associated with this Appletalk port. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

cjnAtPortVlan.name: cjnAtPortVlan
cjnAtPortVlan.description: The vlan associated with this AppleTalk port.

cjnAtPortClearZones.name: cjnAtPortClearZones
cjnAtPortClearZones.description: set to enabled will clear all zones on this at port.

cjnAtPortStateTable.name: cjnAtPortStateTable
cjnAtPortStateTable.description: A list of interface specific Apple Talk Port State Entries

cjnAtPortStateEntry.name: cjnAtPortStateEntry
cjnAtPortStateEntry.description: An cajun Apple Talk Port State instance

cjnAtPortStateIndex.name: cjnAtPortStateIndex
cjnAtPortStateIndex.description: The globally unique value for this Apple Talk Port. This number MUST exist in the cjnIpIfTable ?? to be valid.

cjnAtPortStateDescr.name: cjnAtPortStateDescr
cjnAtPortStateDescr.description: A text string containing information about the port. This string is intended for presentation to a human; it must not contain anything but printable ASCII characters.

cjnAtPortStateNetConfig.name: cjnAtPortStateNetConfig
cjnAtPortStateNetConfig.description: The configuration status of this port.

cjnAtPortStateNetStart.name: cjnAtPortStateNetStart
cjnAtPortStateNetStart.description: The first AppleTalk network address in the range currently used for this port. This is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order.

cjnAtPortStateNetEnd.name: cjnAtPortStateNetEnd
cjnAtPortStateNetEnd.description: The last AppleTalk network address in the range currently used for this port. This is a two octet DDP network address in network byte order. If the network to which this AppleTalk port is connected is a Phase 1 network or a non-extended network, the value for atportNetEnd shall be two octets of zero.

cjnAtPortStateNetAddress.name: cjnAtPortStateNetAddress
cjnAtPortStateNetAddress.description: The AppleTalk network address being used on this port.

cjnAtPortStateState.name: cjnAtPortStateState
cjnAtPortStateState.description: The operational status of this port.

cjnAtFilterTable.name: cjnAtFilterTable
cjnAtFilterTable.description: A list of Apple Talk Filters for this entity.

cjnAtFilterIndex.name: cjnAtFilterIndex
cjnAtFilterIndex.description: An integer that is unique to the Filter that is present in this entry.

cjnAtFilterRowStatus.name: cjnAtFilterRowStatus
cjnAtFilterRowStatus.description: The status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active on this interface. notInService(2) -- Configured on Interface but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface entry NOT FULLY configured. createAndGo(4), -- NOT SUPPORTED. createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)

cjnAtFilterItem.name: cjnAtFilterItem
cjnAtFilterItem.description: When set to the value zone_name(1) this filter applies to zone names. When set to nbp_object(2), this filter applies to nbp object names.

cjnAtFilterOperation.name: cjnAtFilterOperation
cjnAtFilterOperation.description: When set to the value permit(1) objects with this name will not be filtered. When set to no(2), objects with this name will be filtered.

cjnAtFilterString.name: cjnAtFilterString
cjnAtFilterString.description: The ASCII name of the entry to be filtered. When FilterItem is zone_name(1), string is the name of the zone to be filtered. When FilterItem is nbp_object(2), string is the name of the nbp object to be filtered.

cjnAtAccessIfTable.name: cjnAtAccessIfTable
cjnAtAccessIfTable.description: A list of Apple Talk Filters on Apple Talk Interfaces.

cjnAtAccessIfRowStatus.name: cjnAtAccessIfRowStatus
cjnAtAccessIfRowStatus.description: The status of this entry in the table. Note the available states: active(1), -- Obviously Active on this interface. notInService(2) -- Configured on Interface but disabled. notReady(3), -- Interface entry NOT FULLY configured. createAndGo(4), -- NOT SUPPORTED. createAndWait(5) or destroy(6)
